vm.deal		set ETH balance
vm.assume	filter fuzz inputs
vm.prank	fake msg.sender
vm.startPrank	persistent sender

-----

Foundry Flags

--mt [--match-test] "Tells foundry to run only those tests, that match the test function's name. ```forge --mt functionNamewithBrackets```

-----

Stateless fuzzing: random inputs, fresh state each time

Stateful fuzzing: random sequences, same state carried forward

A global invariant is a property that must always hold true for the entire contract/system, no matter what sequence of actions occurs.

-----

Stateful fuzzing: Ending state of previous fuzz run is the starting state of the next fuzz run.

-----

Run a single test file
forge test --mp test/Counter.t.sol

